Global Low-Tension Distribution Board Market Insights
Low-Tension Distribution Board Market size was valued at USD 5.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 8.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Low-Tension Distribution Board Market Overview
The Low-Tension Distribution Board (LTDB) market is witnessing substantial growth, driven by increasing demand for electrical power distribution solutions across various industries. In 2024, the global LTDB market size is valued at USD 7.5 billion and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.2% from 2025 to 2030. The market is being propelled by the rise in infrastructure development, increasing urbanization, and the growing need for reliable power distribution systems in residential, commercial, and industrial sectors. As energy efficiency and safety standards become more stringent, the demand for low-tension distribution boards with advanced features and robust performance is increasing significantly.

